column5: If anybody has seen this before, it deserves watching again and again.  For those that have never seen this, Watch it.  Simply amazing. I have been watching so much of him lately.  Guy has a pair like no other.
that is crazy  I don't know how he could have that much control to know how high off the ground he would be to hit the ballons
that was insane..The Wright Brothers would eat their hearts out..
WOW!! Thought there were a few moments he was going to hit a tree or the ground there!  Unvelieveable!
absolutely incredible !!!!  redbull air racing, skydiving are tame compared to that , adrenaline junkie for sure .... not much room for error in that sport
Big deal. Squrriels have been doing that for a long time.    WOW!
INSANE !!! I wonder how you discover you can do that Bungled suicide attempt

That was posted here last month or so. I must have watched it a dozen times. You can't really tell how fast the dude's going until that camera angle where there's a guy waiting holding up the balloons. It's the kind of clip you can't watch just once.  Thanks.
Wow, crazy stuff.  I like what he says at the end

I saw this guy quite a ways back but never saw this clip. Thats the closest ive ever seen him buzz the ground. Awesome.  He had a documentary called "fearless" that was televised a while back and was talking about how a parachuteless landing was in the works. Something about landing on a ramp that would gradually transition him to a stop. Dunno where that ended up
By what he said at the end I think he too was surprised how close he came to the ground on that one. I also think dude with the balloons needs a new pair of underwear.
